{{multiple issues| {{no footnotes|date=March 2015}} {{one source|date=March 2015}} }} {{Infobox saint |name= Saint Abadios |birth_date= |death_date= |feast_day= 20 January |venerated_in= [[Roman Catholic Church]] |image= |imagesize=150px |caption= |birth_place= |death_place= |titles= [[Martyr]] |beatified_date= |beatified_place= |beatified_by= |canonized_date= |canonized_place= |canonized_by= |attributes= |patronage= |major_shrine= |suppressed_date= |issues= }} '''Abadios''' was a [[martyr]] of the [[Christian church]]. He was born at [[Bilgai]] in [[Egypt]]. He was a native soldier of the army who professed his faith in [[Jesus Christ]] during the reign of [[Diocletian]] at [[Khalakhis]]. He was martyred by being thrown into a rock. His [[feast day]] is on January 20. Information on him can be found in the ''[[Synaxaire Arabe-Jacobite]]''.
==References== *Holweck, F. G. ''A Biographical Dictionary of the Saints''. St. Louis, MO: B. Herder, 1924.
