{{Infobox person | name =Anthony Afolabi Adegbola | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = February 24, 1929 | birth_place = [[Owerri]], [[Imo State]], [[Nigeria]] | othername = | nationality = Nigerian | citizenship = Nigerian | occupation ={{flatlist| * educator *microbiologist *researcher}} | parents = | relatives = | yearsactive = |known for = |awards= | website = }}
'''Anthony Afolabi Adegbola''' was a [[Nigerian]] Professor of [[Animal science]] and former President of the [[Nigerian Academy of Science]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailyindependentnig.com/2015/03/laspotech-signs-deed-gift-idrdg/ |title=LASPOTECH signs deed of gift to IDRDG |work=Daily Independent |accessdate=June 9, 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150707214032/http://dailyindependentnig.com/2015/03/laspotech-signs-deed-gift-idrdg/ |archivedate=July 7, 2015 }}</ref> In 1993, he was elected President of the Nigerian Academy of Science to succeeded Professor [[Akpanoluo Ikpong Ikpong Ette]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nas.org.ng/fellowship/members-of-council/ |title=Members of Council |work=Nigerian Academy of Science |accessdate=June 7, 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150707061854/http://www.nas.org.ng/fellowship/members-of-council/ |archivedate=July 7, 2015 }}</ref>
