'''''Paramecia''''' is a non-mineralized [[Ediacaran]] alga with a differentiated, compartmentalized thallus. This alga probably had multiple phases in its lifecycle, as possible reproductive structures have been identified.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Xiao | first1 = S. | last2 = Knoll | first2 = A. H. | last3 = Yuan | first3 = X. | last4 = Pueschel | first4 = C. M. | title = Phosphatized multicellular algae in the Neoproterozoic Doushantuo Formation, China, and the early evolution of florideophyte red algae | journal = American Journal of Botany | volume = 91 | issue = 2 | pages = 214–227 | year = 2004 | pmid = 21653378 | doi = 10.3732/ajb.91.2.214}}</ref>
